<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1032" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1032">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123B641/18.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I earnestly recommend the diplomatic representatives at Vera Cruz of
                                friendly nations be requested to take action and prompt measures to
                                bring about the release from prison of Vice Consul Silliman at
                                Saltillo, also Consul Bonney at San Luis Potosi, and take them and
                                their American colonies out of the Federal territory. Both Consuls
                                are understood to still be in prison; also several American
                                citizens.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>